  "body": "It would be nice to have support for the [EventListener interface](https://www.w3.org/TR/DOM-Level-2-Events/events.html#Events-EventListener).\n\n[Example on MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget/addEventListener)\n\nSo it wouldn´t be necessary to `bind` the listeners, creating unnecessary copies of the callback for each instance of a component, making use of Event Delegation. \n\nDoes it make any sense?\n\nI´ve made a working proof of concept [in this plunk](https://plnkr.co/edit/q37geDoxuZ5jSkKLvNT3?p=preview)\n\nThis is [my first approach](https://github.com/facebook/react/compare/master...sminutoli:feature/add-event-interface-support) (tests will be added)\n",
